<P>
ASSEMBLY SPEAKER BROWN'S CHARTERED JET PROPOSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Assembly Speaker Willie Brown should be denied his request for a chartered jet 
("Brown Wants State To Rent Jet for Use by Lawmakers," Part I, Aug. 17). 
Lawmakers must suffer the same delays and indignities that their constituents 
suffer at the airports and on the freeways of this state. They need to feel it 
in the seat of their pants, like we do. How else are they going to stay in 
touch with the needs of the electorate? How else are they going to represent us 
and help improve the quality of our lives? 
</P>
<P>
Leadership loses credibility when officials start "requiring" jets, limos and 
other luxuries in the name of busy schedules. You're one of us, Willie! You 
don't like airline congestion? Let us see you in there doing something about 
it! 
</P>
<P>
