<HEADLINE>
<P>
LADY'S HAT LEAVES HIM BRIMMING WITH DISDAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Downey's article, "Giant Hat Gets a Fan Tossed Out," was very insensitive 
to the plight of the fan sitting behind the lady with the large hat. He paid 
for his seat, as did the lady. 
</P>
<P>
Several years ago, I sat behind a lady with a large hat at the Olympic 
Auditorium. I was not able to see the ring, and asked the lady to remove the 
hat. She would not because it would mess up her hair. I asked an usher to 
request that she remove the hat. He did, and she did. 
</P>
<P>
It is just good manners to be thoughtful of your fellow sports fan. 
</P>
<P>
LARRY SANDERS, Whittier 
</P>
</TEXT>
