<P>
LONGEST SHOT WINS FEATURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DEL MAR 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gran Judgement, longest shot in the field of six, held off the late challenge 
of Astronaut Prince and won the $60,000 turf feature a half-length Friday at 
Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Gran Judgement, ridden by Russell Baze, covered the 1 1/16 miles in 1:42 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
The winner, sent off at 12-1, returned $27.80, $8.20 and $4.20. Astronaut 
Prince paid $5.40 and $3.80. Splendor Catch, with Gary Stevens aboard, was 
another length back and paid $3.20 to show. 
</P>
