<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Art 'Censorship' Protest About 200 demonstrators picket the Federal 
Building in Westwood Thursday night while images, including one of a "censored" 
Michelangelo's David, are projected on the building. The march was part of a 
nationwide protest against Sen. Jesse Helms' (R-N.C.) proposed restrictions on 
the National Endowment for the Arts that, protesters charge, amount to 
censorship and content control. A second rally at the Federal Building, set for 
10 a.m. to 2 p.m. today, is to include addresses by political leaders and 
climax in a march along Wilshire Boulevard. (Related story, Page 3.) JEFF SHARE 
