<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE HIGH PRICE OF MASTERING THE TICKET GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Sylvie Drake Aug. 17 article on telephone ticket sales, "Why You Can't Order 
Exact Seats by Phone," Ticketmaster chairman Fred Rosen seems worried that 
transaction times would be prolonged if customers were allowed to learn exactly 
what seats they were getting for their money. 
</P>
<P>
Question: When Ticketmaster phone clerks stretch out transaction times by 
trying to sell subscriptions to the Ticketmaster magazine, is that a good idea? 
</P>
<P>
If you answered yes, congratulations, you're a Ticket Master; if no, well, bad 
news -- you're a Ticket Slave, like me. 
</P>
<P>
DANA ALAN LaFONTAINE 
</P>
<P>
West Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
