<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: $75 MILLION IN DRUGS SEIZED DURING RAIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police and federal agents investigating a network distributing cocaine in 
southeastern Los Angeles County seized more than 400 pounds of the drug worth 
more than $75 million at a Cudahy house early Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Three suspects were arrested, two at the Cudahy house in the 5100 block of 
Clara Street and a third at a house in the 14500 block of Pontlavoy Avenue in 
Norwalk, Huntington Park Police Lt. Paul Catani said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers also found three 9-millimeter automatic pistols at the Norwalk house. 
Both houses were searched about 4:45 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
None of the suspects were named. The operation was a joint effort by police 
from Huntington Park, Ontario and Riverside, and agents of the Drug Enforcement 
Administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
POLICE RAIDS; DRUG SEIZURES; COCAINE; CUDAHY (CA); DRUG ARRESTS -- LOS ANGELES 
COUNTY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082689-0072 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 99512 </DOCID>
