<P>
Dave Chapin of Newport Beach, the second-place finisher in the 1988 Soling 
Class Olympic sailing trials in San Diego, was disqualified and suspended last 
year after testing positive for a banned substance. 
</P>
<P>
The only official announcement of the positive testing was a brief item in the 
current monthly issue of American Sailor magazine, the official publication of 
the United States Yacht Racing Union. The test had been administered under the 
guidelines of the U.S. Olympic Committee. Chapin, skippering the three-man 
boat, was runner-up in the trials to John Kostecki of San Francisco, who later 
won the silver medal at Pusan, South Korea. 
