<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: THREE BROTHERS LEAD DIVISION IN SURFING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three brothers -- Jonathan, Israel and Abraham Paskowitz of San Clemente -- are 
leading the young men's division after Friday's qualifying round of the fifth 
Oceanside Longboard Surfing Club contest. 
</P>
<P>
Leading qualifiers in the men's division (30-39) are Peter Townend of 
Westminster, a former world champion from Australia, and Chris Schlickenmeyer 
and Albert Jenks of Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
Leaders in the masters division (40 and up) include San Diegans Dale Dobson, 
L.J. Richards, Donald Takayama and Skip Frye. 
</P>
<P>
David Nuuhiwa of Torrance leads the nose riding division with a time of 21.6 
seconds. 
</P>
<P>
The quarterfinals of the young men's and men's divisions will be today, along 
with the second round of the masters (40 and up) and the first round of the 
women's division. 
