<P>
HURST TO MISS SUNDAY START 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bruce Hurst was examined Friday by the Padres' medical staff at Scripps Clinic, 
and their diagnosis matched that of Dr. Arthur Pappas, the Boston team doctor 
who examined Hurst Thursday: Hurst might have a slight tear in his groin area. 
</P>
<P>
Hurst missed seven weeks with a groin injury when he was with the Red Sox in 
1986, but said his current injury isn't as bad as the old one. 
</P>
<P>
"It's already a lot better than it was a couple of days ago," Hurst said. 
</P>
<P>
Regardless, Manager Jack McKeon said, Hurst will miss his scheduled start 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Said Hurst: "We'll shoot for Saturday (his next scheduled start) and see how it 
goes." 
</P>
<P>
Don Schulze will replace Hurst in the starting rotation Sunday, opposing Bob 
Ojeda of the Mets. SCOTT MILLER 
</P>
