<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: BUENA PARK; 
</P>
<P>
MAN RUNS FROM POLICE TRAFFIC STOP, IS SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Fullerton man who bolted after being stopped for a minor traffic violation 
Friday afternoon was shot in the hand by police as he fled and was then jailed 
on a felony warrant from Kansas, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A Buena Park police officer stopped a blue pickup truck in a residential area 
at Gardenia Drive and Gladiola Circle, but its 17-year-old driver and Terry A. 
Effinger, 18, its passenger, ran in opposite directions, according to Officer 
Rich McMillen, the department's public information officer. 
</P>
<P>
A passing Cypress motorcycle officer was asked to help, and while chasing 
Effinger fired one shot, striking Effinger's right hand, McMillen said. 
Effinger was later apprehended in the back yard of a nearby residence. 
</P>
<P>
Effinger was taken to a local hospital for treatment of the gunshot wound, 
according to McMillen, who said a check of records showed that he was wanted in 
Kansas on an aggravated assault warrant. 
</P>
<P>
McMillen said the juvenile was found in a nearby carport and apprehended 
unharmed, McMillen said. He was arrested on suspicion of probation violation 
and was taken to Juvenile Hall. 
</P>
<P>
McMillen said it was unknown whether the two suspects had been armed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
